LUMPED-ELEMENT MODEL (0-DIMENSIONAL)
====================================
Assumptions:
• Point objects (no internal fields)
• Single V across, single I through
• No propagation delay
• Time-domain: ODEs only

RESISTOR (R)
Symbol:   ~\/\/~
Law:      V = I * R
Series:   R_T  = R1 + R2 + ...
Parallel: 1/R_T = 1/R1 + 1/R2 + ...

CAPACITOR (C)
Symbol:   | |
Law:      Q = C * V    (I = C dV/dt)
Series:   1/C_T = 1/C1 + 1/C2 + ...
Parallel: C_T   = C1 + C2 + ...

INDUCTOR (L)
Symbol:   ~~~ (coil)
Law:      V = L * (di/dt)
Series:   L_T  = L1 + L2 + ...
Parallel: 1/L_T = 1/L1 + 1/L2 + ...

STRUCTURAL DUALITY
• R & L : additive in series, harmonic in parallel
• C     : harmonic in series, additive in parallel

Valid when circuit size << wavelength.
Beyond that → distributed/transmission line models.

-----------------------------------------------------------

STRUCTURAL DUALITY (SERIES vs PARALLEL)
- R and L: additive in series, harmonic in parallel
- C: harmonic in series, additive in parallel
-----------------------------------------------------------

RDG MAPPING (LUMPED REGIME)
SID: structural primitives R, C, L as 0D objects
PED: dynamic laws (V=IR, Q=CV, V=L·di/dt)
Q-slice: moderates temporal propagation only (no spatial layer)
No MFE geometry; no distributed fields
